EDITORIAL

A post.-Olympic evaluation

Last night marked 17 days since the
Rice Eccles Olympic Stadium hosted the
Opening Ceremonies. Three and a half bil-
lion people worldwide watched the event
with all its pageantry, music and patriotism.
It had been a long haul coming —— from an
embarrassing bidding scandal to slow ticket
sales and security anxieties. Yet the amazing
execution of the Opening Ceremonies wel-
comed the world to Utah and promised an
exciting two weeks of Olympic competition.

Inthe days since, the Olympics have
dished out a wild mix of triumph and disap-
pointment Here’s The Pitt: News’ conven-
tional wisdom on the Olympic highs and
lows.

Sportscasters: § No one expected
unbiased journalism from American com-
mentators, many of whom are former
Olympians and still highly connected to their
sports and the current Olympians. But,
somehow, we didn’t expect them to forget
